RABID-SKWERL-TOOLS

# run the following mel command getenv "MAYA_APP_DIR";
# copy or clone the rabid-skwerl-tools to the following path "** 'MAYA_APP_DIR' **/maya/** mayaVersion **/prefs/scripts"
# add userSetup.py to the directory "** 'MAYA_APP_DIR' **/maya/** mayaVersion **/scripts"
# in the userSetup file, add the path "** 'MAYA_APP_DIR' **/maya/** mayaVersion **/prefs/scripts/rabid-skwerl-tools" to
    the system paths using sys.path.append()
# restart Maya and you should be able to access all the goodies in the rabid-skwerl-tools repository!